{#- =========================================================
   Unified Long Prompt Template (Mixed Image/Video)

   Design goals:
   - Keep the long reasoning-first style from the 0331 long setting.
   - Support both image-text and video-text samples with modality-aware wording.
   - Preserve raw <image>/<video> placeholders from the dataset question.
   - Use <answer>...</answer> for the final answer across task types.
   ========================================================= -#}
{%- if problem is defined -%}
{%- set raw_question = problem -%}
{%- elif content is defined -%}
{%- set raw_question = content -%}
{%- else -%}
{{ 1 / 0 }}
{%- endif -%}
{%- set question = raw_question | replace('\\n', '\n') | replace('/n', '\n') | trim -%}
{%- if problem_type is defined -%}
{%- set ptype = problem_type | lower | trim -%}
{%- else -%}
{%- set ptype = 'open-ended' -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- if data_type is defined -%}
{%- set dtype = data_type | lower | trim -%}
{%- else -%}
{%- set dtype = '' -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- set has_images = images is defined and images is iterable and images is not string and images | length > 0 -%}
{%- set has_videos = videos is defined and videos is iterable and videos is not string and videos | length > 0 -%}
{%- set opts = options if options is defined and options is iterable and options is not string and options | length > 0 else [] -%}
{%- if (dtype == 'video' and has_images) or (has_videos and has_images) -%}
{%- set visual_source = 'video and the accompanying image' -%}
{%- set inspect_instruction = 'Examine the video and the accompanying image carefully' -%}
{%- elif dtype == 'image' or (has_images and not has_videos) -%}
{%- set visual_source = 'image' -%}
{%- set inspect_instruction = 'Examine the image carefully' -%}
{%- elif dtype == 'video' or has_videos -%}
{%- set visual_source = 'video' -%}
{%- set inspect_instruction = 'Watch the video carefully' -%}
{%- else -%}
{%- set visual_source = 'provided visual input' -%}
{%- set inspect_instruction = 'Analyze the provided visual input carefully' -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- if ptype == 'multiple choice' and opts | length > 0 -%}
{%- set full_question = question | trim ~ '\nOptions:\n' ~ opts | join('\n') -%}
{%- else -%}
{%- set full_question = question | trim -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- if ptype == 'multiple choice' %}
{{ inspect_instruction }}, then answer the following multiple-choice question.
First, briefly explain your reasoning based on what you observed in the {{ visual_source }}.
Then, provide the letter of the correct option inside <answer> tags.
Question: {{ full_question }}
{%- elif ptype == 'numerical' or ptype == 'regression' %}
{{ inspect_instruction }}, then answer the following question.
First, briefly explain your reasoning based on what you observed in the {{ visual_source }}.
Then, provide your numerical answer inside <answer> tags.
Question: {{ full_question }}
{%- elif ptype == 'boolean' or ptype == 'binary classification' %}
{{ inspect_instruction }}, then answer the following question.
First, briefly explain your reasoning based on what you observed in the {{ visual_source }}.
Then, provide Yes or No inside <answer> tags.
Question: {{ full_question }}
{%- elif ptype == 'ocr' %}
{{ inspect_instruction }}, then answer the following question.
First, briefly describe the relevant content in the {{ visual_source }}.
Then, provide the recognized text inside <answer> tags.
Question: {{ full_question }}
{%- elif ptype == 'math' %}
{{ inspect_instruction }}, then answer the following question.
First, briefly explain your reasoning and show your work.
Then, provide your final answer inside <answer> tags. If it is multiple choice, provide the option letter; otherwise provide the numerical value.
Question: {{ full_question }}
{%- elif ptype == 'temporal grounding' %}
{{ inspect_instruction }}, then answer the following question.
First, briefly explain your reasoning about when the event occurs.
Then, provide the time span in seconds as a JSON object inside <answer> tags.
Format: {"time": [start_seconds, end_seconds]}
Question: {{ full_question }}
{%- elif ptype == 'spatial-temporal grounding' %}
{{ inspect_instruction }}, then answer the following question.
First, briefly explain your reasoning about when and where the target appears.
Then, provide the time span and bounding boxes as a JSON object inside <answer> tags.
Format: {"time": [start, end], "boxes": {"second": [x1, y1, x2, y2], ...}}
You MUST output one bounding box for every integer second within the time span (inclusive).
Question: {{ full_question }}
{%- elif ptype == 'spatial grounding' %}
{{ inspect_instruction }}, then answer the following question.
First, briefly explain your reasoning about where the target is located.
Then, provide the bounding box as a JSON object inside <answer> tags.
Format: {"boxes": [x1, y1, x2, y2]}
Question: {{ full_question }}
{%- elif ptype == 'tracking' %}
{{ inspect_instruction }}, then answer the following question.
First, briefly explain your reasoning about the target's movement.
Then, provide the bounding boxes as a JSON object inside <answer> tags.
Format: {"boxes": {"second": [x1, y1, x2, y2], ...}}
You MUST output one bounding box for every integer second in the track, up to 32 seconds.
Question: {{ full_question }}
{%- elif ptype == 'code' %}
{{ inspect_instruction }}, then answer the following question.
First, briefly explain your approach.
Then, provide the complete Python code inside <answer> tags. Do not use Markdown fences.
Question: {{ full_question }}
{%- elif ptype == 'svg-code' %}
{{ inspect_instruction }}, then answer the following question.
First, briefly explain your approach.
Then, provide the complete SVG code inside <answer> tags. Do not use Markdown fences.
Question: {{ full_question }}
{%- elif ptype == 'html-code' %}
{{ inspect_instruction }}, then answer the following question.
First, briefly explain your approach.
Then, provide the complete HTML code inside <answer> tags. Do not use Markdown fences.
Question: {{ full_question }}
{%- elif ptype == 'llava' %}
{{ inspect_instruction }}, then answer the following question.
First, briefly explain your reasoning based on what you observed in the {{ visual_source }}.
Then, provide your choice (Response 1, Response 2, or Tie) inside <answer> tags.
Question: {{ full_question }}
{%- else %}
{{ inspect_instruction }}, then answer the following question.
First, briefly explain your reasoning based on what you observed in the {{ visual_source }}.
Then, provide your final answer inside <answer> tags.
Question: {{ full_question }}
{%- endif %}
